Result Builders (previously Function Builders) allow you to create a DSL for building up data structures in a declarative way.  They provide a mechanism to accumulate partial results of computations. Benefits include improved readability, reduced boilerplate, and type safety when constructing complex objects.

Example:
```swift
@resultBuilder
struct StringBuilder {
    static func buildBlock(_ parts: String...) -> String {
        parts.joined()
    }

    static func buildOptional(_ component: String?) -> String {
        component ?? ""
    }

    static func buildEither(first component: String) -> String {
        component
    }

    static func buildEither(second component: String) -> String {
        component
    }
}

@StringBuilder
func createMessage(includeGreeting: Bool, name: String?) -> String {
    if includeGreeting { "Hello, " }
    name
    if let name = name { "!" }
}

let message = createMessage(includeGreeting: true, name: "World") // "Hello, World!"
```
